profile_positions.description:
Lead Auditor for ISO 13485, MDSAP, MDD 93/42/EEC, AIMD 90/385, MDR 2017/745, ISO 9001

Key results:
- successful delivery of 450+ audit days, covering requirements of ISO 13485, MDSAP (FDA, Health Canada, ANVISA, MHLW, TGA), MDD 93/42/EEC, MDR 2017/745 and ISO 9001;
- successful completion of witnessed by Regulators MDSAP audits without observations;
- participation and management of audits in cooperation with Competent Authority (EU-region);
- high number of audit-codes profile based on work and scientific experience;
- high average 9.5+/10 of customers (organizations’) feedback.

Lead Auditor for ISO 13485, MDSAP, MDD 93/42/EEC, AIMD 90/385, MDR 2017/745, ISO 9001

Key results:
- successful delivery of 400+ audit days, covering requirements of ISO 13485, MDSAP (FDA, Health Canada, ANVISA, MHLW, TGA), MDD 93/42/EEC, MDR 2017/745 and ISO 9001;
- successful completion of witnessed by Regulators MDSAP audits without observations;
- participation and management of audits in cooperation with Competent Authority (EU-region);
- high number of audit-codes profile based on work and scientific experience;
- high average 9.5+/10 of customers (organizations’) feedback.

Key results:
- successful directing and managing an R&D group of 9 to 47 HW, SW, process engineers and clinicians with projects budgets from $0.2M till $3.9M;
- design, implementation and management of QMS in compliance with ISO 13485 and 21CFR requirements;
- control of writing and successful transfer of technical files to legal manufacturers and support them during 510(k), CE-mark submission, as well as submissions to local agencies in Russia and CIS-countries;
- timely and budgetary successful management and completion of clinical trials, clinical investigation, and evaluation in cooperation with key hospitals and clinics in Moscow;
- timely and budgetary successful management and completion design transfer to production of listed projects;
- successful completion (timelines and budget) of IQ/OQ/PQ activities related to outsourced production;
- control and management of outsourced production (including development of quality agreements, subcontractor audits, SCARs management);
- successfully raised startup from pre-seed to market clearance and exit.

Completed projects:
- Portable (wearable) Device for monitoring and prediction human functional state;
- Methods of minimally invasive mapping of left atrium micro-rotors based on mathematical processing and analysis of distribution of endocardial region action potentials for subsequent RFA for patients with paroxysmal and persistent atrial fibrillation;
- Software and algorhytms of signals processing for implantable pacemaker.
- Methods for intracardial signals analyzing and prediction of humans critical states;
- Design, development and transfer to the production of coronary bare metal stent;
- Vital signs monitor and standalone software for decision making support for patient functional statement prediction.
- Software and math algorhytms of the patient functional state prediction based on data from vital signals monitors raw data.

Key responsibilities:
- lecturing about basic principles of ECG, electrophysiology, biomechanics of cardio system etc. to bachelors, masters and Ph.D. - program students; 
- creating scientific plans of specialization for bachelors and masters-degree students; 
- public relations for popularization the Department

Product: Digital antenna array for visualization of human organs and tissues

Key responsibilities:
- market analysis and analysis of the possible technical solutions, choosing the optimum one;
- R&D planning;
- preparation of design documentation, preliminary design, schedule and other documentation for digital antenna array for visualization of human organs and tissues;
- development of math methods of images recognition, analyses and simulation in accordance with IEC/IEEE P62704-1;
- formulation of requirements and control of work for electrical circuits and PCBs development;
- specifications’ development for FPGA, PCBs;
- specifications’ development for SW (С++, Perl) for FPGA Xilinx, ADC/DAC (AD, Maxim, LT, TI), MC STM AN1256, quality control and validation of SW
- specifications’ development for housing for digital antenna array for visualization of human organs and tissues;
- preparation for production (SOPs and WIs for all steps of production, technical drawings of housing, PCB, WI for testing, assembling, labeling, quality control, packaging);
- development of specifications;
- evaluation of materials of housing based on economic efficiency, product life time, time of manufacturing (PLA-plastic was chosen for 3D-printing technology);
- evaluation of suppliers of PLA-plastics and purchasing of PLA;
- evaluation of suppliers of 3D-printers (TAZ 4, LULZBOT was chosen);
- design of 3D-model in SolidWorks for transferring to production;
- communication with supplier (accuracy of moulding, surface, technological holes etc.)
- incoming inspection of manufactured mouldings;

Key responsibilities:
- consulting customers; 
- taking participation in tenders; 
- preparing technical specification; 
- assisting in operations procedures (GYN, URO, Coloproctology, Gen Surgery) 
- marketing strategy preparation and implementation

Key results:
- successfully achievements of sales plan in the accountable territory (Moscow);
- increased number hospitals from sales-base in the accountable territory in 2 times;
- sales increasing in accountable area for 31%;
- successful clinical support during operation activities in clinics and hospitals in accountable area.

Key activities and results for completed projects/products: 
- design and development a model of coronary blood flow; 
- design and development of a biomechanical model of the LCA; 
- design and development of spiral stent; 
- design and development of system for rheological (impedance) precardiac mapping
- design and development of system for EEG and SGR analysis;
- design and development of math algorithms, SW and HW parts for optimization of ultrasound knife parameters.

Key responsibilities:
- Marketing Strategy development and implementation;
- Local markets device release and clearance;
- Management of final tests for device release to the local markets (incl hands-on work with the devices):
- Management of installation and servicing activities (incl hands-on work with the devices).

Key results:
- increasing of sales in the accountable territory in 41%;
- completed full-cycle from sales to installation of 15 systems for enhanced external counterpulsation in clinics of Moscow and Astana.

Key responsibilities: 
- Support modalities, analysis and related management regards to technical specification analyses; 
- Cooperation with other Life Care Solution (LCS) modality regarding configuration tools; 
- Providing trainings for customers.

Key results:
- implementation of configurators allowing to reduce time of customer consultation and requirements specification more than 50%;
- optimization of presenting of technical and clinical parameters of vitals signals monitors, anesthesia and ALV-equipment.
